Urinary bladder and paraurethral endometriosis. Authors report a case of bladder and a case of paraurethral endometriosis. The mode of sanitation was by means of TUR and surgery, respectively. Based on the available literary data, the assumptions related to development of the disease its pathology, symptoms and treatment are discussed in brief. Despite the frequency of the disorder, exact diagnosis might take months, perhaps even years. Due to the difficulties in diagnosing this disease, correct diagnosis can be expected from biopsy, as in our case.